com.projetloki.genesis

Class Keyframes

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.projetloki.genesis.Keyframes

  • @PoorBrowserSupport
public final class Keyframes
extends Object
    Defines initial, final and intermediate steps in a CSS animation sequence.

    Example:

     Keyframes kf = Keyframes.from("top: 0;left; 0")
     .through(30, "top: 50%")
     .through(68, "left: 50%")
     .to("top: 100%; left:100%");

 cssBuilder.use(kf);
 cssBuilder.addRule("div.myButton", Properties.builder()
     .setAnimation(
         Animation.on(kf.name())
             .durationSeconds(10)
             .delaySeconds(2)));

    In order to exist in the generated CSS, every keyframe must be registered with CssBuilder.use(Keyframes).

    Keyframes are immutable.

    See Also:
    Animation, MDN, Browser support

      • name

        public String name()
        Returns the name of this keyframes. This is the string you must pass to Animation.on(String).

        If you haven't explicitly specified a name with withName(String), one will be generated automatically.

      • withName

        public Keyframes withName(String name)
        Returns a keyframes instance similar to this, with the given name. If you don't specify a name, one will be generated automatically. Call this method if you want to refer to the keyframes the Javascript.
